list - lists files and directories

Description:
The 'list' command displays all files and directories in the specified directory. Directories are highlighted in blue. If no directory is provided, the current working directory is used. If the directory cannot be opened, an error message is shown.

Usage:
list [<directory_path>]

Examples:
list
list /home/user/Documents
list /nonexistent # Error: Could not open directory '/nonexistent' for listing.
